// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Task - AM_Rog_SL8-9_Task_08 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Dialog - DialogTree 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Page Intro Text :
"P39369717" "<color orange>Operative Vargas furrows his brow, looking at his Arachnos PDA. As you step closer to him, his eyes shoot up to look at you.</color><br><br> Ah, {HeroName}! Welcome, welcome. Have we...met before? Perhaps we have, I deal with so many people in the Isles! My name is Operative Leo Vargas, but please feel free to call me Leo. <br><br>Now, let's see...you're here for the...ah, yes, you're here to help us guard the precious cargo, correct? "
// Answer Text :
"P2991941993" "That's right. What do I have to do?"
// Page InformationPage1 Text :
"P4208050991" "<color orange>Operative Vargas reaches into his belt and pulls out a folded piece of paper. He unfolds it and hands it to you. You read it over...</color><br><br><color Red><scale 1.2>ARACHNOS TERMS AND CONDITIONS</scale><br><br><color OrangeRed>This document will outline the terms and conditions regarding your temporary work for Arachnos. Please read over them carefully and then sign your name on the bottom line. <br><br>1. You will follow all instructions given to you by the highest in command in Arachnos, unless an Arbiter should intervene, in which case the proper rules for following Arbiter laws shall be enforced.<br><br>2. You shall utilize all of your abilities to their fullest extent in order to complete the task given before you.<br><br>3. You will be paid in full once said assignment has been completed.<br><br>4. If you are captured, Arachnos will spend no less than 1 day and no more than 2 weeks to rescue you.*<br><br>5. In the event of being captured, you will deny any affiliation with Arachnos. <br><br>6. Do not attack any members of Arachnos, even if they 'have it coming to them'.<br><br>If you are satisfied with everything in this agreement, please sign on the line below!<br><br><br><scale 0.6>*Time of rescue will depend on how quickly the operative in charge can file the proper papers to be reviewed by a council of Arbiters.</scale>"
// Answer Text :
"P3772362997" "(Sign your name on the bottom line)"
// Page InformationPage2 Text :
"P2087493399" "<color orange>You hand Operative Vargas the signed contract - not that you plan on following it. </color><br><br>Excellent! I'm very excited about this partnership - your abilities are known all around Arachnos and we are all very interested in seeing where this partnership will go. You can go ahead and explore around the warehouse now, get yourself familiar with it. When Longbow is approaching you will receive a notice to assume battle positions. <br><br>I myself must be on my way to file these papers and get other preparations ready. Did you need anything else?"
// Answer Text :
"P3853623297" "Not that I can think of."
// Page InformationPage3 Text :
"P524234928" "<color orange>Operative Vargas shakes your hand firmly before walking off with the contract in hand. You now have free run of the warehouse.<br><br>"
// Answer Text :
"P3628904783" "Time to look around this place..."

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Clue - CrateClue 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Clue Name :
"P1612859071" "Portal Corp Technology"
// DetailString :
"P4040362905" "You found a large device with a blue, glowing sphere in the center. When your hand nears it, the sphere spins very quickly. Looking into the sphere, you can see the images of numerous worlds from other dimensions flash before you in the blink of an eye. <br><br>You're not sure <i>what</i> exactly this is, but it is definitely going to fetch a very high price - somewhere."

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Task Header Items 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// IntroString :
"P4051367409" "Doc Quantum's fall from grace wasn't exactly graceful, per se, given the various experiments he has performed. But the man does have a talent for finding very precious items. Whatever item he has in his possession must be quite important - and pricey. This could be just the thing you need to make a quick buck - or even use it to travel to other dimensions to make more money. <br><br>Given the fact that Doc Quantum is most likely working with Arachnos, you might be able to...trick your way into the base of operations to get what you want. Perhaps by offering your services to help Quantum, you can get in deep enough to steal the items he has."
// AcceptString :
"P1320369054" "Trick Doc Quantum to get Portal Corp tech!"
// SendOffString :
"P2996770700" "You make various calls to set it up so that Quantum and his men will believe you're showing up to be hired off as extra 'muscle' for the deal. They'll never see the betrayal coming. Hopefully."
// ActiveTaskString :
"P2171726752" "Trick Doc Quantum!"
// YoureStillBusyString :
"P1386338546" "Regardless of what happens, this should prove...interesting."
// TaskTitle :
"P51021737" "<font face=title><scale 1.1><span align=center><color orange>Extremely Annoying Ring Tone</color></span></scale></font><br><span align=center><color Yellow><i>Rogue Mission</i></color></span>"

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// MissionDef 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// EntryString :
"P823954762" "You enter the warehouse to see Quantum and Arachnos are preparing things for the arrival of Longbow. You'll have to talk to the liaison first to set things up."
// ExitStringSuccess :
"P1423177822" "<font face=title><scale 1.1><span align=center><color orange>Extremely Annoying Ring Tone</color></span></scale></font><br><span align=center><color Yellow><i>Alignment Mission</i></color></span><br><br>You escaped from the Arachnos warehouse with the technology in hand from Portal Corp. They won't have to send Miss Thystle over now - and you'll be getting something quite nice out of this deal - either money or a chance to go explore some of those alternate dimensions that people have been talking so much about."
// Script Variable NPC_DIALOG_NAME :
"P4108288360" "Operative Vargas"
// Script Variable Greeting :
"P1127431811" "Hello, {HeroName}."

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Objective - Name 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Description :
"P143539114" "Speak with Operative Vargas!"

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Reward - Objective 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Script Variable INACTIVE_DIALOG_MINION1 :
"P1036650868" "Hey, I've been thinking. <em t=4> About life outside of Arachnos. You ever think what it would be like to do what we want? <em t=8> I don't know...forget I said anything, my head is feeling a little fuzzy."
// Script Variable INACTIVE_DIALOG_MINION2 :
"P4293472746" "Oh? <em t=1> What about? <em t=6> That's dangerous thinking... why would you even think that?"
// Script Variable ATTACK_DIALOG_MINION1 :
"P2198878378" "{HeroName} is on the move!"
// Script Variable ATTACK_DIALOG_MINION2 :
"P1575977896" "Stop them!"
// Script Variable INACTIVE_DIALOG_MINION1 :
"P4050519704" "You ever think about your family?<em t=4> Do you believe him?"
// Script Variable INACTIVE_DIALOG_MINION2 :
"P432330964" "I try not to. Phipps tells me that they're taken care of. <em t=7> Do I really have a choice?"
// Script Variable INACTIVE_DIALOG_MINION1 :
"P2418884050" "Did you hear that some Bane Spiders are starting to break off from the mental network?"
// Script Variable INACTIVE_DIALOG_MINION2 :
"P1414761113" "Scary to think about that."
// Script Variable ATTACK_DIALOG_MINION1 :
"P1231086607" "Stop {HeroName} from getting away!"
// Script Variable ATTACK_DIALOG_MINION2 :
"P3542405886" "On it!"
// Script Variable INACTIVE_DIALOG_MINION1 :
"P685275316" "Hey {HeroName}, good to have you on board. <em t=8> Don't mind them. We're all sticking to the rules here."
// Script Variable INACTIVE_DIALOG_MINION2 :
"P432405973" "Hmph. <em t=2> You hurt one of my friends real bad, {HeroName}. Watch your back."
// Script Variable ATTACK_DIALOG_MINION1 :
"P3393248373" "You broke the contract, now you're going to pay!"
// Script Variable ATTACK_DIALOG_MINION2 :
"P730637481" "I've been waiting to beat in {HeroName}'s face!"
// Script Variable INACTIVE_DIALOG_MINION1 :
"P3915716836" "I can't believe Doc Quantum isn't even here. What's his deal?"
// Script Variable INACTIVE_DIALOG_MINION2 :
"P3114731490" "No idea. I don't trust him, personally."
// Script Variable ATTACK_DIALOG_MINION1 :
"P4014718895" "This was all just part of his experiment?!"
// Script Variable ATTACK_DIALOG_MINION2 :
"P4220464652" "I knew we couldn't trust him! Just get {HeroName}!"

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Objective - Crate 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// ModelDisplayName :
"P3524833866" "Crate"
// Description :
"P2317867070" "Steal the Portal Corp Technology!"
